In these examples, we'll take a look at how **Scene Depth** collision can have varying results depending on your camera view compared to **Distance Field** that doesn't rely on the camera view. This is especially noticeable
when moving under an enclosed area, like the tree in this example, where the parts out of view no longer provide collision for the area particle. 



